post_text:
August is Black Business Month. We will be showcasing some of our staff's favorite local Black Owned Businesses! @stacyshawlaw

Check out: Stacy Shaw Law!

Link: https://stacyshawlaw.com

STACY SHAW
Attorney Stacy Shaw is the founding partner of Stacy Shaw & Associates, LLC. She is a native of Wichita, Kansas and a graduate of Harris-Stowe State University in St. Louis, Missouri where she received a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration. While there, Stacy also became a proud member of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc. Alpha Omega Chapter.

Stacy graduated magna cum laude from Thurgood Marshall School of Law at Texas Southern University in Houston, Texas. Prior to founding Stacy Shaw and Associates, Stacy was a litigation and corporate attorney at Smith & Associates, LLC in St. Louis, Missouri. Stacy is passionate about providing widespread access to legal services in the Kansas City Metro area and educating the community about the law.

#blackownedbusiness #blackbusinessmonth #brooksidecharterschool #community # kansascity #KC #local

post_text: We were so excited to work with Lead to Read this summer! Looking forward to another great year with them!
shared_text:
Lead to Read KC
July 13 at 10:50 AM ¬∑

Lead to Read KC is thrilled to be piloting a virtual reading mentoring program to supplement our in-school program! Here's a wonderful endorsement from Kate Smith, a parent of a student in our pilot who also is a long-time Reading Mentor:

"It's fascinating to me to watch organizations figure out how to move forward, so it was fun to see my son have his first virtual reading session with a Lead to Read KC mentor this week. As someone who has read with kids for a while now and loves this time each week, especially with my son's class the past two years, I'm glad we can help pilot a way to continue this program. Who knows what the coming school year will bring, but if you can find a way to help (maybe even with this org), do it! Our kids and our schools need you."

Thank you to Brookside Charter School, Citizens of the World Kansas City and Crossroads Charter Schools for partnering with us on the pilot!
text:
We were so excited to work with Lead to Read this summer! Looking forward to another great year with them!

Lead to Read KC
July 13 at 10:50 AM ¬∑

Lead to Read KC is thrilled to be piloting a virtual reading mentoring program to supplement our in-school program! Here's a wonderful endorsement from Kate Smith, a parent of a student in our pilot who also is a long-time Reading Mentor:

"It's fascinating to me to watch organizations figure out how to move forward, so it was fun to see my son have his first virtual reading session with a Lead to Read KC mentor this week. As someone who has read with kids for a while now and loves this time each week, especially with my son's class the past two years, I'm glad we can help pilot a way to continue this program. Who knows what the coming school year will bring, but if you can find a way to help (maybe even with this org), do it! Our kids and our schools need you."

Thank you to Brookside Charter School, Citizens of the World Kansas City and Crossroads Charter Schools for partnering with us on the pilot!

text:
As stated in an earlier post, Brookside Charter stands against racism. We can not just say that as an organization and not act on it. We have been having beginning conversations and discussing the work needed to better educate our staff and our students. While we are apart we wanted to share some resources with our families to watch with their children around the topic.
